        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="- Comma Splice- A comma splice is when the writer uses a comma instead of a period, semicolon or conjunction to join 2 independent clauses."
            android:id="@+id/textView7"
            android:layout_marginRight="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="20dp"
            android:textColor="#ffffff"/>

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="40dp"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="- Independent clause- These sentences usually contain a subject and a verb. These are sentences that can be used as stand-alone sentences. E.g. Nigel runs in the morning."
            android:id="@+id/textView8"
            android:layout_marginRight="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="20dp"
            android:textColor="#ffffff"/>

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="40dp"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="- Dependent Clause- These are clauses that cannot stand-alone and need another sentence to fully express the thought of the clause."
            android:id="@+id/textView9"
            android:layout_marginRight="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="20dp"
            android:textColor="#ffffff"/>

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="40dp"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="- Semicolon- A semicolon is used to connect two independent clauses that are connected by transitional phrases. A semi colon is not used as a replacement for a comma."
            android:id="@+id/textView10"
            android:layout_marginRight="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="20dp"
            android:textColor="#ffffff"/>

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceLarge"
            android:text="News Articles"
            android:layout_marginTop="90dp"
            android:id="@+id/textView11"
            android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"
            android:textColor="#ffffff" />

        <ImageView
            android:layout_width="340dp"
            android:layout_height="210dp"
            android:id="@+id/imageView6"
